"excerpt_html":null,"excerpt_text":null,"expirydate":-62135596800,"fuzzywordcount":3300,"html":null,"keywords":null,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastmod":1614099600,"objectID":"05210993051f125e30428812e0bb6f94","permalink":"https://mayuresh82.github.io/2021/02/23/edge-controller-part1/","publishdate":"2021-02-23T09:00:00-08:00","readingtime":16,"relpermalink":"/2021/02/23/edge-controller-part1/","section":"post","summary":"2017 was the year of the Software Defined Network (SDN). Apart from other things like new players jumping onto the SDN space and a bunch of new SD-WAN offerings, two prominent innovation leaders - Google and Facebook - both released blogs and papers on their software defined edge network. Google\u0026rsquo;s solution; named Espresso, is likely a more battle tested and production-hardened solution owning to years of R\u0026amp;D and testing. It is, however (or at least in my opinion) a lot more complex than Facebook\u0026rsquo;s Edge Fabric that uses a much simpler approach to solving the same problem - which is to overcome BGP\u0026rsquo;s inability to take link performance ( which translates to application performance) into account for its routing decisions.","tags":["SDN","sflow","controller","bgp"],"title":"Building an Edge Traffic Controller - Part 1","type":"post","url":"/2021/02/23/edge-controller-part1","weight":0,"wordcount":3274},{"author":null,"categories":["General"],"content":null,"date":1608591946,"description":"","dir":"post/","excerpt_html":null,"excerpt_text":null,"expirydate":-62135596800,"fuzzywordcount":2700,"html":null,"keywords":null,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastmod":1608591946,"objectID":"f11136de22f6ade815462fcc44f3b8fb","permalink":"https://mayuresh82.github.io/2020/12/25/nornir_inventories/","publishdate":"2020-12-21T15:05:46-08:00","readingtime":13,"relpermalink":"/2020/12/25/nornir_inventories/","section":"post","summary":"Building Dynamic Inventories in Nornir Organizing your Nornir inventory into multiple groups based 